 ### Failure modes
 
 | Condition                                                          | Behavior |
 |---|---|
-| CDC event arrives before `phase:started`                           | Silently skipped; the catch-up scan reprocesses the writ post-seal. |
-| Dedupe lookup short-circuits on the same `(writId, writUpdatedAt)` | No `evaluate` call, no row, no transition. |
-| `validateConfig` throws                                            | Fail-loud log via the `[reckoner] scheduler:` prefix; evaluation is skipped (no row, no transition). |
-| `evaluate` throws or does not return an array                      | Fail-loud log; evaluation skipped. |
-| Decision carries a `writId` not in the candidate set               | Per-decision `console.warn` naming the offending id; ignore-and-continue. |
-| Two decisions target the same `writId`                             | Fail-loud log; the entire evaluation is skipped (no decision is applied). |
-| Decision carries an unknown outcome                                | Fail-loud log; the decision is ignored. |
+| Tick fires before `phase:started`                                  | Throws fail-loud (`[reckoner] tick: activeScheduler not resolved …`). Production never trips this; tests assert the throw to verify the ordering invariant. |
+| Dedupe lookup short-circuits on the same `(writId, writUpdatedAt)` | The writ never enters the candidate set; no `evaluate` call, no row, no transition. |
+| `validateConfig` throws                                            | Fail-loud log via the `[reckoner] scheduler:` prefix; the entire tick is skipped (no rows, no transitions). |
+| `evaluate` throws or does not return an array                      | Fail-loud log; the entire tick is skipped. |
+| Decision carries a `writId` not in the candidate set               | Per-decision `console.warn` naming the offending id; ignore-and-continue (the tick still applies in-scope decisions). |
+| Two decisions target the same `writId`                             | Fail-loud log; the entire tick is skipped (no decision is applied for any candidate). |
+| Decision carries an unknown outcome                                | Fail-loud log; the decision is ignored (sibling decisions still apply). |
 
